#
#  Maintained by Neng-Fa Zhou (CUNY Graduate Center professor,
#  Brooklyn College CS faculty, B-Prolog creator).  19 GH stars
#  on picat-lang/picat (small academic community).  Picat is a
#  MULTI-PARADIGM logic-based programming language combining
#  Pattern-matching + Intuitive functions + Constraints + Actors
#  + Tabling (memoization) into one rule-based language.  Distinct
#  from pure Prolog: Picat predicates/functions/actors are
#  defined with PATTERN-MATCHING rules (Erlang/Haskell style)
#  rather than unification, but RETAIN explicit unification +
#  non-determinism as features when wanted.  Used for constraint-
#  satisfaction problems (CSP), combinatorial optimization,
#  symbolic computation, and is a popular ACADEMIC TEACHING
#  language for logic+functional+constraint programming courses.
#  Has built-in support for SAT/SMT solvers (Espresso, Maple,
#  Lingeling, Geas).  Implementation is hybrid: VM written in C
#  (the "Toam" / "B-Prolog VM" engine, originally Zhou's earlier
#  B-Prolog system), library and user code written in Picat
#  itself.  Sister tools: prolog (SWI-Prolog — in corpus via
#  _prolog + STOCK on most distros), swipl (SWI-Prolog CLI — in
#  corpus via _swipl), gprolog (GNU Prolog — in corpus via _gprolog
#  + STOCK), trealla (Trealla Prolog), scryer (Scryer Prolog),
#  ciao-prolog (Ciao Prolog research), minizinc (constraint
#  modeling — in corpus via _minizinc), gecode (constraint engine
#  — in corpus via _gecode), or-tools (Google OR-Tools — in
#  corpus via _or-tools), clp(z) / clpfd (constraint libs).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 1st Picat CLI library —
#  Picat's **HAND-ROLLED C SWITCH-BASED PARSER** in `emu/init.c`
